The difficulties inherent in effectively teaching information system development, or systems analysis and design, have been dclcumented time and time again [FR187,KAN88,UNG87,YAV87]. The author of this paper has designed a series of HyperCard applications (to run on Apple Macintosh computers) to help illustrate a number of the current topics in the information systems curriculum, including decision support systems, expert systems, end user computing, and prototyping. Preliminary results indicate that this software can make a significant contribution to th,~ success of a systems analysis and design